inn1.comm: appeal for a lbw straightaway! Gets a lot of inward movement and traps him on the pads but down the leg side
this time he doesn't control the radar and the ball slides down the legside
142.9 kph, seemed quicker than that, lands outside off and he's happy to let that go
144 kph, big inswing again, hurries the batsman and the ball clips his pads and lobs up
tempts him with a full and wide delivery outside off and he goes for a flashy drive and misses
full on middle and leg and pushed down to mid-on, tells his partner to stay back
shuffles and clips him down to square leg
lands it on a good length on the off stump and he defends
slides down the leg side and he tickles it down to fine leg off his pads, just beats Ramdin
whoopsy! Gets a thick leading edge which just beats point, extra bounce there
lands it on a good length wide outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
defends with soft hands and the ball drops somewhere near the crease
good shot, full and sat up outside the off stump waiting to be hit, he plays an elegant drive off the front foot and beats the big gap between mid-off and cover
good length on the off stump and defended down the pitch
gets behind the line and pats it back to the bowler
full on the pads and clipped down to midwicket
angles across the left-hander and he defends with soft hands
just keeps it on the channel outside the off stump and he's happy to let it go
clips him down to square leg and tells his partner to wait
pace and bounce, caught Watson by surprise there, he tried to cut it but the ball suddenly reared up off a good length, close call!
drops it down to the off side with soft hands
defended off the back foot to gully
clips it to midwicket and Marsh stops in his tracks from the other end
stays behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler
Watson gets impatient and tries to hoick it away over the on side, he fails to time the pull and the top edge just clears the infield, two fielders charge after it
angles across the left-hander and he leaves it to the keeper
fullish in length on the off stump and he pushes it down to mid-off
angles it on the pads and he clips it with the line to fine leg
stays back and defends down the pitch back to the bowler
gets beside the line and steers him wide of the slips down to third man
full in length outside off and he steers it down to point
full on the stumps and defended down the track
he capitalises on the width outside the off stump, bends his leg slightly and steers it past the gap between cover and point, nice timing
pitching it full isn't working for West Indies, gift on the pads and he shows a straight bat and pushes it effortlessly past mid-on
beats him outside off with a slower ball, good comeback by the bowler
pushes it wide of the bowler and takes a quick single to mid-on
stays back and pushes it down the pitch
pushes it with soft hands down to mid-off and sets off for a quick single, good calling
slower ball and he tries to dab it down to third man but gets a thick outside edge which drops short of the keeper
drops it short of a length on the middle stump, he swivels and pulls over square leg, that's Watto's favourite shot
opens the face and steers it down to third man
angles it on the pads and he clips him wide of midwicket
stays behind the line and defends down the pitch
angles it on the pads and he clips it down to deep midwicket, Pollard throws and hits the stumps direct at the striker's end but the batsman's home
short and pulled firmly but Pollard's there at deep square leg to mop up
full and driven back down the pitch, Rampaul tries to deflect it to the stumps but the ball rolls to mid-off, the batsmen think of a single

clips it down to deep midwicket and Simmons gives the chase, he fires a quick throw to Rampaul who whips off the bails but the batsman is just home, the third umpire takes a look, good pickup and throw  by the fielder
lands it outside off and he's happy to let it go
stays beside the line and cuts to point
cuts again but finds point
chops it down to point again, like an action replay
default mode, no I'm not pressing the rewind button, chops it down to point again
breaks the monotony with a firm drive off the front foot wide of mid-off, full outside off and spanked away
drops it short and angles it on the body, he bends his knee slightly, gets on top of the bounce and pulls to long leg
punchy drive down the pitch and the fielder at mid-on sprints across and cuts it off
stays beside the line and defends
gets beside it and angles him down to point
open the face of the bat and angles him down to third man
slower ball on the pads and he clips him down to midwicket
gets beside the line and softly taps it to the off side

careless shot really, Smith teases him with a wide delivery on a fullish length outside off, Marsh stays at the crease and chases it, drives away from the body and gets a thick edge, very straightforward take for Ramdin
angles it on the pads and he clips it to midwicket, Simmons fumbles
full on middle and leg and defended back to the bowler
slower ball outside off and he dabs it just wide of point
full outside off and tapped just in front of point and sets off
shout for an lbw, lunges forward to defend but the ball swings back in and hits him outside the line of off, Bowden shakes his head
excellent sliding stop at point, the fielder flings himself to his right and saves a few runs for sure
pushes it to the off side
angles it on the body and easily worked away down to fine leg
stays back and punches it towards midwicket
gets across his stumps and taps him down to midwicket
firmly driven but well stopped by short cover, the West Indian fielding has been impressive save for one misfield at midwicket
forward and pushed down to short cover
exquisite! Ponting comes down the pitch early and Smith pitches it up for his liking, lofts him elegantly just over the long-off rope, that's 2000 runs at the MCG for Ponting
on the pads and he clips him away down to fine leg, 2 leg byes
gets beside the line and steers him to the off side
shuffles and clips him to the off side
143 kph, just short of a length and he gets his elbows high to defend
143.5 kph, pitches it up and he pushes it to the off side
shuffles and tucks him away down to square leg
chops it down to short third man for a single
on the backfoot, he stays back and punches it down to mid-on and sets off for a quick single
stays beside the line and taps it to the off side
slower ball outside off and he bends down and carves it over backward point, seemed like he would spoon it straight to the fielder
good length outside off, Ponting gets on the front foot and defends
full outside off and pushed to short cover
pulls to short midwicket and mistimes the shot
bowls it flat and quick and he drives down to cover
full again and driven down to sweeper cover
slower through the air and drops it on a good length, he stays back and cuts to point
full on the stumps and driven back to the bowler
gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
full on the pads and worked down to mid-on
full on the pads and clipped down to deep square leg
stays beside the line and defends to the off side
pushes it down to point
full on the pads and pushed down to mid-on
poor delivery, down the leg side and it beats everyone, including short fine leg
drops it short and he plays a short arm pull down to deep midwicket
short outside the off stump, Watson gets onto the back foot and cuts it for a single
fuller on the middle stump. Ponting comes forward and defends it on the leg side
outside the off stump. Ponting comes forward and drives it to extra cover for a single
a touch short on the middle and leg. Watson bends down a touch and pulls it to deep midwicket for a single
outside the off stump. Ponting comes forward and pushes it to short extra cover
fuller outside the off stump. Ponting again  drives it to the same fielder
on the off stump and coming back in. Watson closes the face of the bat and pushes it to the leg side
fuller outside the off stump. Watson drives and a misfield by Gayle at cover allows them a single
good length delivery on the middle and leg as Ponting pushes it to long-on for a single
brute strength there as Watson picks a fuller delivery on the off stump and lofts it over the infield on the leg side
on the middle stump. Watson punches it to long-on to give Ponting the strike
outside the off stump. Ponting opens the face of the bat and runs it to sweeper on the off side for a single
outside the off stump. Ponting comes forward and pushes it on the off side for a single
short outside off. Watson cuts it to point
on the middle stump. Watson punches it to long-on
Outside off. Ponting comes forward and drives it to long-off for a single
Watson comes forward and defends a ball on the middle stump
outside off, cut to point for a single
not quite short enough to pull and so he mistimes it down to deep square
full on the off stump and driven down to mid-off
full on the pads and he pushes it down to deep square leg
full and driven down to extra cover
full on the pads and clips him down to midwicket
good length outside off and he cuts to sweeper cover
full on the off stump and driven to the off side
flighted on the pads and clipped to the on side
makes a lot of room too cut but he nearly slices it on the full to Smith at point
full on the pads and clipped down to midwicket
full outside off and driven to cover
pounds it down the pitch, Gayle gets across to stop it
swings and misses, just sneaks past his off stump
stays back and cuts him down to sweeper cover

Gayle fumbles a run-out opportunity! The ball is played to deep midwicket and the throw from Simmons is fast and accurate but his captain makes a royal mess of it, Watson turned back, slipped and was yards out of his crease when the throw reached Gayle
gets forward and drives to cover
nice shot, flighted outside off and he chips down the track and he scoops him over extra cover, beats the fielder in the deep
gets forward and drives to cover
Miller flings himself to his right and saves a straight drive
gets forward and drives him down to sweeper cover
punches it down the pitch and the bowler tries to intercept the drive but the ball beats him
flat and quick and pulls him down to square leg
slower through the air and driven wide of point
full on the off stump and jammed back to the bowler
forcefully driven down to long-on
clips it past midwicket for a single
hits that to downtwon Melbourne! Chips down the track on seeing the flight and he carts him several rows over long-off
full outside off and driven to point
jogs the single to deep extra cover
flat and quick and he pulls him down to deep midwicket
tucks it towards square leg
pushes it to sweeper cover
he clubs a full toss down to deep midwicket, should have found the rope
not quite short enough but he heaves it to the on side
down the leg side and he tries to paddle it away
flighted on middle and leg and he pulls to square leg
pulls him to deep midwicket and he pushes hard for the second run

well bowled there, he bowled it much flatter and dropped it a bit short too on sensing Watson's intentions, he gave him the charge but didn't get to the pitch of the ball, lands down Morton's throat at long-on
full on the pads and clipped to midwicket
full on the off stump and driven down to short mid-off
full on the off stump and driven to sweeper cover
drops it with soft hands to the off side and sets off
full outside the off stump and driven to the off side
stays back and pushes him to mid-on
stays back and taps him down to long-on
flatter delivery and pushed through the line to long-on
on the pads and clipped down to deep square leg
chips down the track but clips him to Pollard at midwicket
tucks it straight to Pollard again
comes down the pitch, action replay, Pollard in action again
Pollard strikes! a back of length ball that jags in and takes the inside-edge with the Australian captain looking to drive off the front foot, and takes out offstump
Pollard greets White with a bouncer, that was only 122.8 kmh, but it climbed sharply, white ducks under
another shortish ball, White stands tall and guides the ball towards backward point
defended towards mid-on this time
drops the ball towards the wicketkeeper, and thinks about taking a single, but decides against it
well outside off, left alone
full on the pads and clipped to midwicket
drops it back to the bowler
gets forward and clips him to midwicket
flatter delivery,clipped to square leg
low full toss outside off and he pushes it down to long-off
gets across and the ball clips his pads  and rolls to the off side
defends him down to point
full outside off and driven to long-off
full on the pads and clipped down to midwicket
shuffles and works him down to square leg
full outside off and pushed down to deep cover
down the leg side and he bends his knee and gently paddles it down to fine leg
Clarke was distracted by something after Gayle had delivered and he backed away, it's called a dead ball but Clarke's withdrawal was quite delayed
clipped to deep square leg
full outside off and driven down to mid-off
gets forward and pushes it just wide of mid-off
gets beside the line to a fuller length ball and he steers it down to deep point
pushed it down to short cover
good slower ball, he tries to pinch a single to point but the fielders are alert
taps it down to short cover
drops it on a good length outside off and he cuts to deep cover
stays back and punches him to long-off
slower through the air, rocks back and cuts to sweeper cover
tries to slam it through the off side but finds short cover
full on the off stump and driven back to the bowler
flighted on the pads and pushed back to the bowler
full on the off stump and driven towards cover
drops it short of a length outside off and he cuts to deep point
spoons it in the air and the ball just drops short of Gayle at short extra cover
tucks it down to deep square leg
stays back and punches it to the off side
punches it down to sweeper cover and White makes the mistake of not grounding his bat while completing the first  run
short of a length and he punches him down to cover
gets on his knee and paddles him down to fineleg
gets forward and drives to cover
full outside off and driven down to cover
stays back and punches him down to deep cover
clipped to the on side and it's drinks
short of a length outside off and pulled to midwicket
short and wide again and

just after the drinks break! Pollard doesn't bowl that with much pace, lands it wide outside off and Clarke can't resist the drive, plays away from the body and everyone including Bowden thought there was an edge, replays aren't conclusive though
drops it towards gully and sets off quickly for a single
full outside off and pushed to the off side
138.5 kph, gets forward and knocks it to the off side
good running, he just drops it in front of point and sets off immediately
144.3 kph, that too a yorker, Hussey slips and falls at the crease as he works it to the on side
excellent running again from White, drops it wide of point and charges off
driven firmly back to the bowler, Roach gets a hand to it
full outside off and squeezed down towards point for a single
full on the stumps and driven firmly down the pitch
drops it short and he swivels and pulls him down to deep square leg
full outside off, White defends it back to the bowler
full on the off stump and driven down to long-off
comes round the wicket and bowls it full, he pushes it down to sweeper cover
pushed it down to long-on

good catch by Ramdin but he's in pain! Good anticipation rather, White tries to pull a slower ball dug in short, he swings too early and the ball clips the toe of the bat and heads towards Ramdin's right, the keeper moved to his left at first but quickly moved the other way keeping his eyes on the ball, takes it one handed on the dive
after that good catch Ramdin messes up and lets the ball go right between his legs, Roach bowls a low full toss and the batsmanm swings and misses, Ramdin fumbles
152.5 kph, that was quick, beats him on the drive outside the off stump
nips back in and he defends it softly
gets beside the line and taps it down to short cover
the slower ball bounces a bit more and beats him on the drive, nearly takes the edge
drops it towards point for a single
slower ball outside off and he drops it to the off side
opens the face and dabs it down to third man for a quick single
glides it to third man and the throw is just wide of the stumps
pushes it down to short third man
steers it towards point with soft hands and sets off
tucks it to square leg off his pads
outside off and he angles it down to third man
slower ball and he shovels it down the pitch and the ball rolls to long-on
aims for the yorker length and he jams it out to long-off
full on the pads and he squirts it to point
comes round the wicket, he gets behind the line and defends back to the bowler
Hussey tries to pull that short ball but takes his eyes off the ball, he's hit flush on the grill
slower ball on middle and off and driven down to long-on
full on the off stump and pushed to long-off
slower ball down the leg side, too wide for Haddin to paddle that across

Pollard appeals for a return catch but Haddin's not sure so he stands his ground, Pollard bowls a slower ball almost on a yorker length and Haddin jams his bat on the pitch and spoons it back, Pollard moves to his right on his follow through and takes it one-handed, Bowden asks the third umpire and replays show that it was straightforward, the ball did not touch the pitch after it spooned off the bat
full on the pads and worked to the on side
good yorker, Johnson just manages to squeeze it out
jams out another yorker but Roach can't stop it, long-on picks it up
drifts on the pads and he clips him towards square leg
full on the stumps and pushed down to wide long-on
full toss on the leg stump and he clips it to square leg
full outside the off and squeezed to the off side
that's a cracker of a drive, half volley outside off and he leans forward and drives powerfully wide of extra cover
drops it on a good length and he swivels and pulls to deep square leg
clips it to deep midwicket and Simmons fumbles, that allows a second run
poor delivery, the fine leg was up and he bowled it down the leg side, all Hussey had to do was to gently tickle it away to the boundary
gets beside the line and steers it to the off side
150 kph, quick full toss outside off and he taps it towards cover
squirts it down to mid-off for a quick single
pulls on one leg to square leg and Hussey charges out of his crease and quickly tries to hurry back, the throw from Dowlin was to the bowler but Roach was nowhere near the stumps
works it away to the on side for a single
lovely shot, good length on the pads and he picks the gap at deep midwicket by pulling on the backfoot
slower ball on the pads and whipped to square leg
full on the off stump, makes room and tries to cream it through the off side but finds mid-off
on the pads and he works him down to short fine leg

another drive away from the body gives a catch to Ramdin, Husset makes a bit of room to slice it hard through the offside, may have been a slower ball, too early on the shot and the thick edge it taken by the keeper after diving forward
full outside off and driven towards cover
on the pads and he whips him away down to deep midwicket
makes room and crashes a low full toss straight to point
fast yorker at 150 kph, outside off and Hauritz hardly saw that
makes room and he follows him by bowling it on the blockhole outside leg, squirted to mid-on
high full toss perhaps just below the waistline, Johnson pulls to midwicket
backs away and jams out a fast yorker to point
shot of the evening so far! Johnson makes room to club a low full toss on the leg stump and he times it so well that the ball nearly carries all the way over deep midwicket
drives him down to deep extra cover
full on the stumps and driven down to long-on
makes room to bash that away past point but he swishes at thin air and the ball sails over the middle stump
good ball, takes the pace off the ball and Johnson makes a lot of room to swing that over the on side, the ball clips his pads and goes to the keeper
makes room to dig it out to the on side but he misses it, beaten for pace and the yorker ball thuds on to his leg stump
makes room and swings him across the line, the ball rolls behind square on the on side and they scamper two

inn2.comm: starts with a 134kmh bouncer, too high for the umpire's liking
shortish and into the ribs, Gayle swats that down to fine leg, great timing, nearly through to the fielder in the deep, lands a few yards short of him though
nearly a wicket there, Morton gets an inside edge and the ball bounces just in front of the stumps and sails over
Morton again defends unconvincingly, another inside edge, the ball rolls towards the off side, Gayle was haring through for the single and was nearly at the striker's end when Morton responds
short ball, Gayle takes a big swish at it, eyeing the midwicket boundary, but doesn't connect
this time the short ball is on legstump, Gayle lifts his front leg as he helps the ball just over Shaun Marsh at square leg, the sun was in Marsh's eyes which might have saved Gayle
again Bollinger digs it in, another flat bat swipe from Gayle, bottom-edges it just wide of a diving Haddin to the fine leg boundary
Morton plays his third unconvincing shot, he's slow on his stroke and inside-edges the ball onto his boot
much more solid this time, shows the full face of the bat as he defends back towards the bowler
shaping into the batsman, length delivery, 148kmh, punched towards mid-on
back of a length and outside off, Morton gets nicely forward and defends, that ball was 144kmh
length ball outside off, Morton jabs at it and guides it past slip and towards third man
Harris sends down a length ball at 145kmh, pushed off the front foot to mid-on

Bollinger has struck, that's the end of Gayle, yet another short ball, Gayle went for the pull, gets a top-edge and the ball swirls towards mid-off, Johnson was setting off to his right initially and had to change direction and run backwards before collecting the catch just outside the circle
Morton defends cautiously off the backfoot, gets behind the line of a short of length ball
length ball outside off, eased towards mid-off off the front foot
shortish ball outside off, slapped towards cover
not sure Morton was watching that all the way, a bouncer and Morton slugs it towards square leg, straight towards the fielder
length ball outside off, defended back towards the bowler
Dowlin faces his first ball, well outside off and he shoulders arms

nearly a run-out there, Harris pegs Dowlin onto the backfoot with a short ball, Dowling fends it to the leg side, Harris races across in front of the non-striker and gets to the ball, and nearly throws down the stumps at the non-striker's end, Dowlin would have been a goner if that hit

punched back to the bowler, and there's more good fielding from the bowler, Morton is on all fours as he tries to scrambles back into his crease after playing the shot, Harris opts to not throw the ball

and Harris continues to find international cricket easy, another wicket for him, this one was in the channel outside off, Morton goes for the drive and gets a faint edge through to the keeper, he walks
Simmons gets a 148kmh delivery first up, defends watchfully
short of length and outside off, Simmons gets forward and pushes the ball towards cover
full delivery outside off, Dowlin defends to the off side

Windies are collapsing, Dowlin joins the procession, it was a delivery angling across the batsman, pitching outside off and going away, the batsman gets well forward and wafts away from his body, gets the outside edge to second slip
low full toss on off, carved though covers by Deonarine, mistimed though so it doesn't go all the way to the boundary
Bollinger keeps it tight outside off, Deonarine pokes it behind backward point
great carry through to the keeper, short of length ball angling across the batsman, who lets it through to Haddin
pegs away at offstump, Simmons defends off the front foot, gets a bit of an inside-edge, the ball dribbles to the leg side
back of a length ball, heading for offstump, 145.9kmh, blocked off the backfoot
similar delivery, 146.4kmh this time, more backfoot dfefence, this time towards the bowler
messes up his line this time, well down the leg side, it was a shortish ball but died on its way to the keeper, too low for a diving Haddin to collect
clipped towards square leg, calls for a single but there's no response
length ball outside off, driven towards cover off the front foot
another delivery down the leg side
gets his line right this time, angling across the left-hand batsman, who is happy to leave the ball to the keeper
shortish ball, steered towards backward point and a tight single is taken
on the legstump, brushes Deonarine's thigh pad and loops past the keeper on the way to the fine leg boundary
length ball on off, solidly defended towards mid-off
back of length and homing into offstump, more solid defence from Deonarine
a repeat of the previous delivery, a touch slower though, 129kmh where the previous one is 140-plus, blocked to the leg side
just slightly wide outside off, pushed towards cover off the backfoot
back to pegging away at off, defended towards point this time
length ball bowled from wide of the crease, slanting into offstump, pushed back towards the bowler
defends with a slightly open face towards the off side, that was another tight delivery on offstump
on middle and off this time, opens the face of the bat to guide the ball towards cover
143kmh, Simmons is beaten by that one, in the channel outside off, Simmons was looking to defend to the off side but ended up playing inside the line
a touch shorter from Harris, Simmons gets forward and pushes the ball towards mid-on
first ball that is not targetting offstump this over, easy leave for Simmons as that delivery was a couple of feet outside off, that's a maiden for Harris
starts with a shortish ball outside off, 143.8kmh, Deonarine slashes it uppishly over backward point for four
length ball and pretty wide outside off, umpire must have thought about that before deciding to not call it a 'wide'
gets it much closer to off this time, 145kmh, slapped towards point
another back of length ball just outside off, Deonarine shuffles across and turns it behind square leg in an ungainly manner
short of length again, heading for offstump, blocked to the off side, Simmons thinks of the single but decides against it
full and wide, Simmons is tempted into a cover drive, he misses and the ball scurries through to the keeper
starts off with a 126kmh, back of length on the pads, tucked towards short fine leg
lovely stroke from Simmons, short and wide, cuts that powerfully behind point, Johnson does the fielding in the deep
back of a length outside off, pushed towards cover off the front foot, Watson seems a little easier to deal with after the three express bowlers before him
length ball outside off, a confident front-foot cover drive, straight at the fielder
angling into offstump, punched towards mid-on, Simmons again takes a couple of steps for the single but turns back
length ball well outside off, left alone by Simmons
batsman shoulders arms to a wide delivery outside off
fullish and on offstump, defended back to the bowler
146.3kmh bouncer, Deonarine thought of the pull but decides to duck under instead
Johnson presents a half-volley and Deonarine clubs that past extra cover for four, splendid shot
Johnson shortens the length, keeps the line on off, Deonarine blocks towards point
length ball outside off, Deonarine content to leave that one
length ball on off, Simmons walks across the stumps to clip the ball towards the leg side
mistimes a backfoot drive towards cover, taht was a short of length ball outside off
similar length but a bit of width for Simmons, who steers the ball towards third man
a slower full ball just outside off, driven down towards mid-off, where a diving Harris does the fielding
short of length, keeps it in the corridor outside off, defended to the off side by Simmons
similar delivery, Simmons crunches it towards point, straight at the fielder, so there's no time for a single
full ball just outside off, 147kmh, left alone
another 147kmh delivery, short and not much width but Deonarine hammers that past White at point for four, White just about got a hand on that one but couldn't stop it
shortish ball on the pads, clipped towards square leg
144 kmh bouncer, Deonarine spots it early and ducks

Deonarine has played some good cuts today, but this time he can only find Ponting at backward point, superb catch from Ponting, timing his jump perfectly as he latched onto that overhead chance, great captaincy as well, Ponting wasn't in that position at the start of the over, came in only after the previous cut for four
148.4 kmh first ball, Pollard was late reacting, it was short of a length on middle, Pollard just about gets his bat down to send the ball rolling towards square leg
Simmons opens the face and pokes the ball towards Ponting at backward point, there's a direct hit but Pollard has made his ground
well outside off, left alone by Pollard
closer to off this time, but Pollard is again not interested, Haddin collects
length ball just outside off, Pollard drives it crisply towards mid-off
Pollard isn't going to hang around, especially in the Powerplays, that was a length ball outside off, Pollard clubs that over mid-on for four, not too well timed but enough to send it for four
this time some finesse from Pollard, shuffling across the stumps and tucking the ball behind square leg for a couple, batsmen should have pushed for a third there
dabbed towards point for a single
148.4kmh, that was too quick for Pollard, manages to defend it though off the backfoot
not to short from Johnson, but Pollard opts to sway out of the line of the ball, dropping his wrists and it sails through past offstump to the keeper
quick, back of length ball down the leg side, Pollard scuttles across the stumps to get out of it's way
pitched up and outside off this time, Pollard is quickly onto the front foot and caresses that one in front of point
full and wide, much slower from Johnson, 132.6kmh, doesn't  bounce much and it's touch take for Haddin, bouncing the second time just in front of him, he gives away a couple of byes
well outside off, and left alone by Simmons, and Billy Bowden calls 'drinks'
back of length ball heading for offstump, defended off the front foot
similar delivery, driven firmly towards mid-off for a single
on middle and leg this time, tucked towards square leg
Watson keeps it short of a good length, outside off this time, driven towards cover
fuller this time, just outside off, Simmons works it away towards square leg

an uncommon sight that, a misfield from an Australian fielder, it was Ryan Harris who let the ball through at long-on as he looked to pick up the ball, Pollard had driven the ball there but not with his trademark power
fuller on middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler
bottom hand comes off the bat as Simmons looks to drive that ball past covers, doesn't beat the fielder
shortish on middle stump, Simmons jumps and turns the ball towards midwicket, sprints through for a single after that
full and outside off, left alone by Pollard
on legstump, just back of a length, Pollard was looking to tuck that to square leg, deflects it onto his pads instead

a stfiled appeal for caught behind, Pollard looks to glance the ball, but seems to have missed it, Haddin was sure that was out and started running towards the stumps, only then did he start to appeal and he's bemused when it is turned down and the ball called a wide as well
down the leg side, looks to play it towards square leg, gets it on the pads and the ball dribbles towards backward point
Simmons clips the ball from offstump to just in front of square leg
fuller outside off, pushed towards the off side off the front foot
length ball outside off, driven towards cover off the front foot
angling across the batsman, full delivery, left alone by Simmons and that's a maiden for Bollinger
fullish ball, driven down to long-off, all along the ground
well outside off, Simmons looks to paddle-sweep that one, he misses as does Haddin
Simmons plays this one with soft hands towards backward point and pinches a single
a wristy on-drive to a full delivery sends the ball scurrying towards long-on
a touch short from Hauritz, Simmons is quickly onto the backfoot and slashes that one past backward point, superb timing from Simmons and played very, very late
same length but not as much width as the previous ball, Simmons plays a similar stroke, but doesn't beat backward point
full and just outside off, punched towards mid-on
short ball on middle stump line, Pollard swivels and pulls it towards deep square leg
length ball heading for off, Simmons drops the ball to the off side and the batsmen zip through for a single
length ball pitching outside leg, might have hit Pollard just outside leg as well, dribbles behind square leg
back of length, again heading for off, Pollard defends the ball to the leg side
a bit of a mishit form Pollard, short of length ball on middle and leg, Pollard swings that wide and over mid-on, he doesn't need to time the ball perfectly to get it to the boundary
short and wide, carves it past backward point
full ball just outside off, steered towards backward point
full nad outside off, gets nicely onto the front foot and driven past covers
Simmons loves the cut shot, another slightly wide ball, Simmons eyes the areas around point but can only bottom-edge it and it goes to the keeper on the bounce
played off the front foot towards cover
overpitched and well outside off, Simmon paddle-sweeps the ball very fine down the leg side
Simons guides it past backward point for a single
another single, this time by turning the ball behind square leg
back of a length, no room at all for the batsman, Simmons drops it to the off side and sprints for the single
just outside off, Pollard deftly dabs the ball towards third man for a single, Pollard looking in good touch here
'Noooo' is the scream from both batsmen after Simmons opens the face to steer the ball towards backward point
a touch short, and a bit of width as well, helped towards covers for a single
full and wide, Simmons drives uppishly wide of long-off, doesn't time it too well, but it lands safely
another full delivery, on the stumps this time, defended towards the off side
quick single taken by pushing the ball towards point
Pollard looks to defend off the front foot but is beaten as the ball slips past the outside edge
back of a length, turning into offstump, clipped behind square leg for an ambled single
short ball, 142.8kmh, Pollard swings it around to deep square leg
back of a length and just outside off, driven towards cover point
same length, this time the ball is on middle and off, turned towards fine leg, Pollard hurries through the first run to have time for the second
another short ball, pulled to square leg easily
swing and a miss to a fullish ball outside off
short of length on offstump, played with soft hands towards cover, batsmen wisely decide to not chance a single
length ball just outside off, gets a bit of an outside edge towards backward point
fuller and on middle and off, defended back down the pitch
overpitched and eased down to long-on for a single
flighted delivery, full and wide, Simmons slaps it towards cover

that's the end of Pollard, this shot would have been a six in many international ground, Pollard clubbed that one powerfully, but gets a bit too much height, Johnson is there at the long-on boundary, positioning himself nicely to take the catch a few metres inside the rope, that was in the air a long time
Simmons likes the paddle-sweep to the ball which is well outside off, gets it towards short fine leg
starts with a shortish ball on offstump, guided towards backward point
a bit of width, the batsman throws his bat at it, Ponting dives at backward point to field

and another big blow for West Indies, with that their slim hopes are gone, Simmons was looking to guide that length delivery towards third man but gets a thick edge to the keeper, the ball kept low but Haddin clings on to it after diving to his right
Smith slaps his first delivery towards point
short ball and well outside off, Smith flails at it but doesn't connect
length ball outside off, batsman shoulders arms
this one kicks up off a good length, fends it off is body to the on side
rises up on him again and he flicks it towards square leg
fullish in length outside off and driven firmly to mid-off
stays back and taps it down with soft hands
gives him width outside off and he opens the face and dabs him down to third man
full on the middle stump and pushed towards mid-off
nice timing on that one, fractionally short outside off and he plays a short arm pull across the line and beats midwicket, looked like two runs at first but the ball sped away from Bollinger
opens the face and dabs it behind square on the off side
slower ball and he tries to bang that outta here but he's beaten
gets beside the line and taps it to the off side
good shot, he drops it short and he picks the length early, swivels and clubs it over square leg
pushes it down to mid-off
pretty close to offstump, but the batsman decides to late cut it, gets it towards short third man
just back of a length on legstump, defended back towards the bowler
full and quick, angling across the batsman, who lets it through to the keeper
that one was too quick for Smith, 147 kmh, Smith was looking to defend off the back foot but the ball slips through between bat and body
short of length ball outside off, powerfully slapped towards backward point where Ponting fields
bowled from wide of the crease, going way down the leg side
again from wide of the crease, full and outside off, punched beautifully through the gap between mid-off and extra cover
Harris plugs away at a back of a length, just outside off, pushed towards cover
same length, no width again for the batsman, defended off the backfoot
once more on the same length, on middle and leg, defended towards short midwicket, Ramdin was racing for the single but had to stop and turn back, a direct hit would have caught him short
shorter and on legstump, clipped towards square leg
fullish and outside off, a thick outside edge sends the ball towards Johnson at third man
slanting into middle stump, defended watchfully towards the bowler
Ramdin again steers a ball close to offstump towards backward point
looks to drive towards mid-off, gets an inside edge towards square leg
length ball well outside off, Ramdin gets on one knee and sweeps
and that's the end of Smith, not the best shot form Smith, sweeps a ball uppishly from well outside off, finds Watson at deep midwicket
length ball on off, pushed towards midwicket
Miller looks to slam his first ball through extra cover, doesn't connect
Harris gets another wicket, that one stayed low after bouncing short of a length, Ramdin was taken by surprise, and couldn't get his bat in the way to let the ball crash into offstump
fullish ball on middle, driven towards the off side
back of a length on off, guided towards backward point
edged towards third man off the backfoot
another outside edge, again to third man
driven off the front foot towards point
way outside the offstump, just within legal limits
full and wide, Miller gets it away past backward point for two
taps the ball towards the leg side
gets well forward and blocks the ball
a quick single is stolen after the ball is pushed towards cover
full ball on off, swept towards square leg
homing into offstump, defended off the backfoot
similar delivery, Rampaul tries to make room and cuts it towards point
checks his shot this time, steering the ball towards third man
pegging away at a short of length, on offstump, defended towards point
slower ball, 126kmh, full delivery just outside off, defended towards the off side
third for Harris, and another catch for Haddin, no footwork at all from Miller as he wafts at the ball outside off, gets a thin edge which just about carries to Haddin, one more to wrap this one up
Hauritz fires it into the pads, defended to the leg side

Australia go 1-0 up, Rampaul sweeps without too much power behind the shot, the ball loops to Shaun Marsh at deep midwicket, simple catch and West Indies go down by 113 runs, Gayle's 4-1 prediction looks implausible now, Australia picked up their sixth straight ODI win this summer
